<subSubSection pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 74" captionStartId="F74" captionText="Figure 74. Distribution of Conostegia caelestis." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure74" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96432" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">74</figureCitation>
). Known from Mexico through Guatemala and Belize to Honduras from sea level to 1000 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="974185" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure74" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96432" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" start="Figure 74" startId="F74">
<paragraph pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Figure 74.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia caelestis" order="Myrtales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caelestis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Conostegia caelestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia caelestis" order="Myrtales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caelestis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Conostegia caelestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from its congeners on the basis of its dense indument of stipitate stellate hairs especially on the leaf abaxial surface, inflorescence and hypanthia. As 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
noted, this species has a very definite flowering time and is never fruiting at the same time that it is flowering, suggesting a long maturation time for the berries. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia caelestis" order="Myrtales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caelestis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Conostegia caelestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the dense indument of stipitate stellate hairs with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia brenesii" order="Myrtales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brenesii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Conostegia brenesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but they are not closely related. See further discussion of their differences under 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia brenesii" order="Myrtales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brenesii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Conostegia brenesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
